SPINSTRAWINTO GOLD broke half a beat slow, vied for the lead two wide and between horses leaving the first turn, but gave way passing the half mile pole, weakened around the far turn, was eased up in upper stretch, then received assistance from the outrider to return to his connections and walk off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WICKED ROSE was off a bit slow allowed to settle while racing from the rear of the field along the rail, trailed until the quarter pole, made a late run, passed several but at the eighth pole still had three more to over come, was kept too task and driven and passed two more, and finally caught the leader with no time top spare was up for the win all while in the four path. DRILLING REPORT was wide into the first turn settled into the second tier along the backside, matched strides with the leader around the half mile pole, continued to battle out of the turn and into the stretch, shook that competitor at the three sixteenth pole, looked like the winner but was caught late. DREWHUSTLE was strong for the first half mile of the race while being rated, was pressured around the half mile marker by an outer foe, matched strides through the turn and into the lane and gave way at the three sixteenth pole. BIND FAITH was off slow, was allowed to settle going into the first turn, started to slowly gain ground from the outside and was in contention at the three eighths pole, gave a game effort early in the stretch but flattened out late. OAK HILL SOLUTION vied for the lead early finally settled for mid pack at the six furlong pole, traveled along the rail with horses on the out side of him, shuffled back at the three eighths pole and started a steady retreat but was able to pass a tired rival in the lane. PLAY MO was aloud to find his stride early along the rail, shifted out into the three path at the five furlong pole, moved up in between rivals after the half, was asked for more run and did so willingly into the turn from the inside, was still giving good effort out of the turn but faded by the eighth pole.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STRUMMER laid off of the pace in the six path into the first turn, tucked down to the four path in the early stages of that bend, came under a firm hold behind rivals down the backstretch, shifted back outside of foes nearing the far turn, gained six wide around that bend, took aim on the clear leader while shifting inwardly through upper stretch, brushed an inner counterpart approaching midstretch, sustained a bid at the sixteenth pole, and forged an advantage late. FOR REAL ALICE pressed outside of the leader and from the three path, vied with a half mile remaining, led narrowly from her inner counterpart in the two path around the far turn, drew clear entering the lane, maintained a clear margin well into the final furlong, but was caught in the final sixteenth, and saved place. HEART THAT BINDS laid off of the pace in the five path, inched closer along with an outer rival around the far turn, took brushes from that foe while being forced down a path in upper stretch, kept on while getting outkicked by that foe in the final furlong, and just missed reaching place. MY LITTLE JEN tracked along the inside, vacated the rail into the far turn, searched for racing room in the two to three paths while pocketed among rivals turning for home, but yielded back from crowded quarters entering the lane, and kept on mildly thereafter. POINT OF VICTORY trailed two wide, lagged behind around the far turn, cut the gap entering the lane, swung six wide in upper stretch, and moved up on her left lead. STORIED TRIP saved ground far back, encountered traffic turning for home, then lacked a bid. LAKE RUNNER required subtle correction from the assistant starter in the gate to become set for the start, showed the way while remaining a bit off of the rail around the first turn, got headed by an outer presser at the half mile pole, sustained pressure around the far turn, but gave way nearing the lane. EXPLOSIVELY HOT stalked two wide, then from between horses down the backstretch, chased four wide while among rivals around the far turn, and gave way turning for home.
